      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle and take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1681912048665-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1681912048665-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1681912048665-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1681912048665-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1681912048665-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop 1/3 of your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> finely and roughly chop the remainder</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in<strong> </strong>300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1681912054053-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1681912054053-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1681912054053-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1681912054053-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1681912054053-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, add your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to the pan and cook for 3 min on each side or or until lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1681912058628-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1681912058628-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1681912058628-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1681912058628-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1681912058628-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>spinach</strong>, most of the <strong>coriander</strong> (save a few leaves for garnish!) and the <strong>roughly chopped chilli </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Blitz until very finely chopped – this is your <strong>arroz</strong> <strong>verde base</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681912062495-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681912062495-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681912062495-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681912062495-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681912062495-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is lightly browned, add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>arroz</strong> <strong>verde base</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong>, give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681912067357-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681912067357-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681912067357-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681912067357-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681912067357-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for an initial 20-25 min or until the rice and chicken are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the rice is looking a little dry!</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>mayo</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chilli</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>green chilli mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1681912071097-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1681912071097-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1681912071097-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1681912071097-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-3-1681912071097-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice and chicken are cooked, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Gently stir it all together and cook for a final 2-3 min or until warmed through – this is your <strong>one-pot</strong> <strong>arroz verde & spiced chicken thigh</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-4-1681912074934-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-4-1681912074934-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-4-1681912074934-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-4-1681912074934-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-4-1681912074934-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one-pot</strong> <strong>arroz verde & spiced chicken thigh</strong> drizzled with the <strong>green chilli mayo</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong> and season generously with <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
